main event: A witness observed a large oval object, about the size of a house, hovering about 30 feet above the ground in Liberty Center, Ohio on January 6, 1966.
interesting points: The object suddenly went down and touched the ground, then disappeared completely within a minute.
The witness said the object looked as though it were on the horizon and was completely out of sight within a minute.
There were no photographs or physical evidence of the sighting.
Other civilian witnesses in the area reported similar sightings of strange objects in the sky.
The sighting lasted for about 10 minutes.
sighted object: a large oval object, about the size of a house
